params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Required. The project, organization or folder on which to execute the request. The format is: projects/[PROJECT_ID_OR_NUMBER] organizations/[ORGANIZATION_ID] folders/[FOLDER_ID]

params.name: data.filter
params.description: Required. A monitoring filter that specifies which time series should be returned. The filter must specify a single metric type, and can additionally specify metric labels and other information. For example: metric.type = "compute.googleapis.com/instance/cpu/usage_time" AND metric.labels.instance_name = "my-instance-name"

params.name: data.interval
params.description: Required. The time interval for which results should be returned. Only time series that contain data points in the specified interval are included in the response.

params.name: data.aggregation
params.description: Specifies the alignment of data points in individual time series as well as how to combine the retrieved time series across specified labels. By default (if no aggregation is explicitly specified), the raw time series data is returned.

params.name: data.secondary_aggregation
params.description: Apply a second aggregation after aggregation is applied. May only be specified if aggregation is specified.

params.name: data.order_by
params.description: Unsupported: must be left blank. The points in each time series are currently returned in reverse time order (most recent to oldest).

params.name: data.view
params.description: Required. Specifies which information is returned about the time series.

params.name: data.page_size
params.description: A positive number that is the maximum number of results to return. If page_size is empty or more than 100,000 results, the effective page_size is 100,000 results. If view is set to FULL, this is the maximum number of Points returned. If view is set to HEADERS, this is the maximum number of TimeSeries returned.

params.name: data.page_token
params.description: If this field is not empty then it must contain the nextPageToken value returned by a previous call to this method. Using this field causes the method to return additional results from the previous method call.
